            <text>
                <body>
                    <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                        <ab>
                          <lb n="1"/><persName type="ruler" key="Ptolemaios IV" ref="#egypt"><w lemma="βασιλεύς">βασιλεῖ</w> <name nymRef="Πτολεμαῖος">Πτολεμαίωι</name> <w lemma="Φιλοπάτωρ">Φιλοπάτορι</w></persName>
                          <lb n="2"/>καὶ <persName type="ruler" key="Arsinoe III" ref="#egypt"><w lemma="βασίλισσα">βασιλίσσηι</w> <name nymRef="Ἀρσινόη">Ἀρσινόηι</name></persName>
                          <lb n="3"/>τὸ <w lemma="ὕδρευμα">ὕδρευμα</w> καὶ τὸ <persName type="divine" key="Nymphai"><rs type="institution" subtype="public_space" role="dedication" key="hieron" ref="#itanos"><w lemma="Νυμφαῖον">Νυμφαῖον</w></rs></persName>
                          <lb n="4"/><rs type="institution" subtype="official" role="builder" key="phrourarchon" ref="#itanos"><persName type="attested" key="Leukios f. Gaios"><name nymRef="Λεύκιος">Λεύκιος</name> <name nymRef="Γάιος" type="patronymic">Γαΐου</name> <placeName ref="#rome" type="ethnic">Ῥωμαῖος</placeName></persName> <w lemma="φρουράρχων">φρουράρχων</w></rs>.
                          </ab>
                    </div>
                    <div type="commentary">
                        <p>La dedica di un acquedotto ed un Ninfeo a Tolemeo IV e Arsinoe III è frutto dell’iniziativa del romano Lucio figlio Gaio, <foreign>phrourarchon</foreign> della base militare tolemaica di Itanos (sulla quale cf. <ref type="ins" target="#ic3_4_2"><title>IC</title> III 4 2-5</ref>, <ref type="ins" target="#ic3_4_9">9</ref>, <ref type="ins" target="#ic3_4_14">14</ref> e <bibl><ref target="#b1740">Spyridakis 1970</ref></bibl>). Un altro comandante del <foreign>phrourion</foreign> lagide compare più tardi nel corso del II secolo a.C. come dedicante in <ref type="ins" target="#ic3_4_14"><title>IC</title> III 4 14</ref>, in questa circostanza con il titolo lievemente differente di φρούραρχος.</p>
                <p><emph>Elementi istituzionali o altri termini rilevanti</emph>: <ref type="inst" target="#hieron"><foreign>hieron</foreign></ref>, <ref type="inst" target="#phrourarchon"><foreign>phrourarchon</foreign></ref>.</p>
                    </div>
